[30;1m151 | [0m[35m    Replacement for builtin open() that reads unicode even in ASCII environment[0m
[30;1m152 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m153 | [0m[35m    In order to read unicode from text, python uses locale.getpreferredencoding[0m
[30;1m154 | [0m[35m    to translate bytes to str. If the environment only provides ASCII encoding,[0m
[30;1m155 | [0m[35m    this will fail since most office files contain unicode.[0m
[30;1m156 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m157 | [0m[35m    Therefore, guess a good encoding here if necessary and open file with that.[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m19[0m[34m of [0m[33m1880[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m87 | [0m[35m    Ensure that print()ing unicode does not lead to errors.[0m
[30;1m88 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m89 | [0m[35m    When print()ing unicode, python relies on the environment (e.g. in linux on[0m
[30;1m90 | [0m[35m    the setting of the LANG environment variable) to tell it how to encode[0m
[30;1m91 | [0m[35m    unicode. That works nicely for modern-day shells where encoding is usually[0m
[30;1m92 | [0m[35m    UTF-8. But as soon as LANG is unset or just "C", or output is redirected or[0m
[30;1m93 | [0m[35m    piped, the encoding falls back to 'ASCII', which cannot handle unicode[0m

[30;1m11 | [0m[35mEncryption/Write-Protection can be realized in many different ways. They range[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35mfrom setting a single flag in an otherwise unprotected file to embedding a[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35mregular file (e.g.  xlsx) in an EncryptedStream inside an OLE file. That means[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35mthat (1) that lots of bad things are accesible even if no encryption password[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35mis known, and (2) even basic attributes like the file type can change by[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35mdecryption. Therefore I suggest the following general routine to deal with[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35mpotentially encrypted files::[0m

[30;1m694 | [0m[35mmalware analysis and detection (potential Indicators of Compromise): IP[0m
[30;1m695 | [0m[35maddresses, e-mail addresses, URLs, executable file names.</p>[0m
[30;1m696 | [0m[35m<p>It returns a list of tuples containing two strings, the pattern type,[0m
[30;1m697 | [0m[35mand the extracted value. (See the malware example above)</p>[0m
[30;1m698 | [0m[35m<p>Sample usage:</p>[0m

[30;1m334 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m337 | [0m[35mExcel chart into a Word document. In general, OLE objects cannot trigger[0m
